<taxonomicName box="[151,386,1392,1418]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Tachydromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luang">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,386,1392,1418]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Tachydromia luang</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1467,1656]" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">
The group can be distinguished from other species groups by the following combination of characters: palpus yellow (rarely brownish yellow), lacking silvery hairs; prothoracic sclerites finely pollinose (except 
<taxonomicName box="[1323,1417,1507,1532]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Tachydromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luang">
<emphasis box="[1323,1417,1507,1532]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">T. luang</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); usually 
<number box="[244,259,1547,1573]" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" value="2.0">2</number>
notopleurals; vein R 
<number box="[505,513,1563,1577]" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[523,530,1563,1577]" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" value="3.0">3</number>
straight. It should be added that the wing pattern is very variable within this group. The presence of a ventral process on the right epandrial lamella of the male terminalia is likely a synapomorphy of the 
<taxonomicName box="[353,447,1630,1655]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Tachydromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luang">
<emphasis box="[353,447,1630,1655]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">T. luang</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group.
</paragraph>
